context: Each cardinal takes on a titular church, either <a0_0>a church in the <b2_0>city of Rome or one of the suburbicarian sees<b2_0/><a0_0/>. The only exception is for patriarchs of Eastern Catholic Churches. Nevertheless, <b1_0>cardinals possess no power of governance nor are they to intervene<b1_0/> in any way in matters which pertain to the administration of goods, discipline, or the service of their titular churches. They are allowed to <b3_0>celebrate Mass and hear confessions and lead visits and pilgrimages to their titular churches<b3_0/>, in coordination with the staff of the church. They often support their churches monetarily, and many <b4_0>Cardinals<b4_0/> do <b5_0>keep in contact with the pastoral staffs of their titular churches.
